OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 19 Apr to Tue 28 AprFA
OL,6,Ffew showers around at the start of the
OL,7,Fperiod, mainly affecting the far
OL,8,Fnortheast of the UK. For many though
OL,9,FSunday should be fine and dry with
OL,10,Fspells of warm sunshine. Into the
OL,11,Ffollowing week fronts associated with
OL,12,Fanother Atlantic low will try to push
OL,13,Finto the UK, but may struggle to make
OL,14,Finroads against an area of high
OL,15,Fpressure to the northeast and are
OL,16,Flikely to be held at bay. So for much
OL,17,Fof next week plenty of dry weather
OL,18,Fwith sunny spells. Some E coasts could
OL,19,Fbe on the chilly side, but further
OL,20,Fwest temperatures likely feeling quite
OL,21,Fwarm. Toward next weekend and beyond
OL,22,Flikely turning more unsettled with a
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Freturn of some rain or showers for
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fmany.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
